article.description: The Houston Comets continued the road woes of the New York Liberty.
article.headline: Thompson and Swoopes too much for N.Y.
article.story:
HOUSTON (Ticker) -- The Houston Comets continued the road woes 
of the New York Liberty.

Tina Thompson scored 15 of her 20 points in the decisive second
half as the Comets handed the Liberty their seventh straight
road loss, 61-53.

Thompson's turnaround jumper with 9:21 remaining put Houston in
front for good, 41-39, and sparked a 10-3 burst. Janeth Arcain
and Sheryl Swoopes each had four points during the run, which
was capped by Swoopes' layup with 3:44 to play.

New York climbed within 57-53 in the final minute on
back-to-back layups by Tari Phillips and Vickie Johnson. But
Thompson made four free throws down the stretch to seal the
Comets' third straight victory.

Arcain finished with 14 points on 7-of-9 shooting and Swoopes
and Michelle Snow chipped in 10 apiece for Houston, which shot
44 percent (23-of-52) and limited New York to 36.5 percent
(23-of-63).  The Comets have won seven of their last eight.

Johnson made 7-of-13 shots and scored 14 points, but the rest of
the Liberty shot just 32 percent (16-of-50). Phillips
collected 12 points and 16 rebounds, but New York has not won on
the road since a 70-60 triumph at Minnesota on June 6.
